9 An Act relating to poultry feeding operations;
authorizing the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture,
10 Food, and Forestry to suspend certain construction
and operation on newly registered or licensed poultry
11 feeding operations; providing exception; authorizing
Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and
12 Forestry to conduct certain inspection; requiring
Department to cease registration or licensure under
13 certain circumstance; providing for promulgation of
rules; providing for codification; and providing an
14 effective date.
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 10-9.4a of Title 2, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. Beginning on the effective date of this act, the Oklahoma
21 Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry shall suspend the
22 construction or operation of poultry feeding operations registered
23 for less than one (1) year of operation or that have undergone a
24 transfer of ownership within one (1) year of operation until such
Req. No. 1686 Page 1

1 time as the Department determines compliance with all poultry
2 feeding operation rules and regulations.
3 B. The provisions of this section shall not apply to existing
4 poultry feeding operations that have been in continual operation for
5 more than one (1) year after the effective date of this act;
6 provided, however, the Department shall be authorized to review,
7 inspect, or investigate existing poultry feeding operations, and, if
8 such review, inspection, or investigation results in a penalty
9 pursuant to Section 10-9.11 of Title 2 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the
10 Department shall issue a cease and desist order of the violating
11 poultry feeding operation by notice pursuant to Section 10-9.11 of
12 Title 2 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The Department shall not reissue
13 a registration for any operation whose certification was revoked
14 pursuant to this subsection.
15 C. The Department shall promulgate any rules necessary to
16 implement the provisions of this section.
17 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 20-44a of Title 2, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. Beginning on the effective date of this act, the Oklahoma
21 Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry shall suspend the
22 construction or operation of new concentrated animal feeding
23 operations licenses for persons engaging in poultry feeding
24 operations for which registration is not required pursuant to
